# WsServer package  MIT (c) 2020 miktim@mail.ru
Lightweight WebSocket Server
preRelease

Release notice:
  - java SE 1.8+;
  - in accordance with RFC-6455: https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6455;
  - WebSocket extensions not supported;
  - localhost self signed certificates do not work.

Overview:
  Constructors:
    WsServer();
    WssServer();

    Constants:
      String WSSERVER_VERSION;
      int DEFAULT_SERVER_PORT;
      int DEFAULT_CONNECTION_SO_TIMEOUT;
      int DEFAULT_MAX_MESSAGE_LENGTH;
    Methods:
      void createContext(String path, WsHandler handler) throws URISyntaxException;
      void bind(int port);
      void bind(InetSocketAddress sa, int backlog);
      void setConnectionSoTimeout(int millis);
      void setLogFile(String logFile) throws IOException;
      void setMaxMessageLength(int len);
      void setKeystore(String jksFile, String passphrase);
      void start() throws Exception;
      void stop();
  
  Interface:
    WsHandler  see: https://github.com/miktim/WsServer/tree/master/srcs/WsHandler.java

  WsConnection:
    Constants:
      WebSocket closure codes see: https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6455#section-7.4
    Methods:
      String getPath();
      void send(String message) throws IOException;
      void send(byte[] message) throws IOException;
      int getClosureCode();
      void close();
